WEBVTT

00:02.127 --> 00:03.617
ANNOUNCER:
Previously on Smallville:

00:03.795 --> 00:06.286
MARTHA:
We didn't ﬁnd him, he found us.

00:06.506 --> 00:08.167
[TIRES SCREECH]

00:08.550 --> 00:09.881
I could've swore I hit you.

00:10.051 --> 00:13.760
-So, what are you? Man or superman?
-I haven't ﬁgured it out yet.

00:13.930 --> 00:16.512
JOR—EL:
You are the last son of Krypton.

00:17.058 --> 00:19.515
CLARK: What are you trying to say?
I'm from another planet?

00:19.686 --> 00:23.679
I don't know how I'm supposed to be
the man he wanted without him here.

00:24.024 --> 00:25.764
-Who are you?
-Lois Lane.

00:25.942 --> 00:27.648
JIMMY:
I've seen how you look at each other.

00:27.819 --> 00:29.605
Lois and Clark would be great together.

00:29.779 --> 00:32.111
I'm the newest recruit
to the Daily Planet.

00:32.282 --> 00:34.989
To me you're more than just a hero.
You're a superhero.

00:35.160 --> 00:37.446
I am the villain of the story.

00:37.620 --> 00:38.700
Lionel's here.

00:38.872 --> 00:40.408
I'm not the Lionel you knew.

00:40.582 --> 00:42.994
TESS: Lex is dead.
LIONEL: That is a lie.

00:43.168 --> 00:45.159
TESS:
You're all engineered from Lex's DNA.

00:45.336 --> 00:48.669
When I sent the Kandorians away,
I opened a door for something else...

00:48.840 --> 00:52.003
...to come to Earth. It preys upon
the dark side we already have.

00:52.177 --> 00:54.168
GODFREY:
Now our unholy trinity is complete...

00:54.345 --> 00:56.210
...preparing the way for Lord Darkseid.

00:56.389 --> 00:58.095
You won't remember any of this.

00:58.558 --> 01:02.517
The Omega's a sign of corruption.
A mark that the darkness has taken over.

01:02.687 --> 01:06.475
-What if one of us were to get infected?
CLARK: If we can't stop it...

01:06.649 --> 01:09.311
...the darkness will infect
every person on this planet.

01:10.320 --> 01:12.652
-Gold meteor rock.
-It could take away his powers.

01:12.822 --> 01:15.074
You could be the greatest hero
the world's known.

01:15.241 --> 01:17.857
CLARK: Not according to Jor-El.
JONATHAN: Then do what you do best:

01:20.830 --> 01:23.742
...but the rest of the world does,
and I decide my fate!

01:23.917 --> 01:26.158
JOR-EL:
Your journey is far from over.

01:26.336 --> 01:27.371
Goodbye, Jor-El.

01:28.505 --> 01:30.917
ANNOUNCER:
And now, the series ﬁnale of Smallville.

01:32.467 --> 01:38.588
"This is the story of an amazing boy
who grew up in the ﬁelds of Kansas...

01:39.474 --> 01:43.558
...in a little town called Smallville.

01:45.647 --> 01:49.105
When he became a man, he believed
the only way to seize his destiny...

01:49.275 --> 01:51.812
...was to turn his back
on both his parents...

01:51.986 --> 01:55.945
...and refuse to see the darkness
descending on Earth.

01:56.116 --> 01:58.732
But all that was about to change.

01:59.536 --> 02:02.744
He was about to face
his greatest challenge."

03:34.756 --> 03:36.963
Some people take time off
when it's their wedding day.

03:37.133 --> 03:38.794
[ELEVATOR BELL DINGS]

03:42.305 --> 03:45.968
There is no wedding. Don't pretend
you didn't hear what I said last night.

03:48.394 --> 03:50.476
And you're one to talk.
That blue underoo...

03:50.647 --> 03:53.639
...sticking out of your collar means
you're on the job too.

03:54.525 --> 03:57.517
l was keeping busy.
I didn't wanna crowd you.

03:57.820 --> 04:00.527
You know, you haven't called
in eight hours.

04:01.032 --> 04:04.320
Usually you ﬁgure things out
when I give you some space.

04:06.788 --> 04:08.653
Or you can just keep avoiding me.

04:08.831 --> 04:11.994
I'm not avoiding you.
l have work to do.

04:12.168 --> 04:14.375
The president just arrived
for a fundraiser...

04:14.545 --> 04:17.457
...plus a huge stack of police reports
just came in.

04:17.632 --> 04:19.338
And l have to call all the guests...

04:19.509 --> 04:22.421
...and let them know
that the big day has been cancelled.

04:25.556 --> 04:27.012
Nice try, speedy.

04:27.183 --> 04:28.844
But you can't make 411 disappear.

04:29.018 --> 04:30.303
[WHOOSH]

04:32.397 --> 04:33.682
[SIGHS]

04:35.566 --> 04:37.693
Your Copperﬁeld act is impressive...

04:37.860 --> 04:39.725
...but it won't change my mind.

04:41.322 --> 04:42.983
Go out there and save the day.

04:43.157 --> 04:44.738
Wherever it needs saving.

04:44.951 --> 04:48.159
Lois, there's a team of heroes out there
protecting the world.

04:48.329 --> 04:49.705
So we can get married.

04:51.165 --> 04:52.826
You really don't see it, do you?

04:55.878 --> 04:58.494
You're a hero
and that's how it should be.

04:59.215 --> 05:02.878
You've gotten so used to the fact
that you know you're gonna be able...

05:03.052 --> 05:05.759
...to ﬁx everything
and make everything right...

05:05.972 --> 05:10.215
...that you cut out any possibility that
there are some things that you just—

05:10.727 --> 05:11.967
You can't ﬁx.

05:14.564 --> 05:16.350
We don't need ﬁxing.

05:17.567 --> 05:19.398
We don't.

05:20.737 --> 05:23.228
But we are in an impossible situation.

05:24.115 --> 05:26.902
One that you can't super-speed...

05:27.201 --> 05:30.785
...or super-hear
or super-leap your way out of.

05:32.248 --> 05:36.537
Clark, every minute
that you spend with me...

05:37.045 --> 05:40.879
...having dinner,
arguing about paint colors...

05:41.049 --> 05:44.041
...arguing about whether or not
to get married...

05:44.802 --> 05:47.088
...you could be out there
saving someone.

05:47.805 --> 05:50.968
Lois, this is my future,
and I want you to be a part of it.

05:51.142 --> 05:53.599
Yeah, well,
maybe we don't get what we want.

05:54.062 --> 05:56.428
I'm just in your way.

06:05.156 --> 06:08.444
You're not in my way, Lois.

06:09.786 --> 06:10.946
You're by my side.

06:15.291 --> 06:17.247
If you really wanna cancel
the wedding...

06:17.418 --> 06:20.034
...you're gonna have to leave me
standing at the altar.

06:39.774 --> 06:41.981
Who knew tying the knot
was so much work?

06:42.151 --> 06:45.814
You gotta remind me to thank Zatanna
for making our nuptials so hassle-free.

06:45.988 --> 06:49.025
I would've liked to have remembered
some details of our wedding.

06:49.200 --> 06:54.285
Considering the details of that night,
all I really need is a marriage license.

06:55.331 --> 06:58.198
-You know, I was wondering if you--
-I was gonna ask you—

06:58.376 --> 07:00.367
-Sorry, you can go—
-You should go ﬁrst.

07:00.586 --> 07:02.122
Go ahead.

07:02.505 --> 07:06.373
If Zatanna hadn't put you under that spell,
would you still have, um...?

07:08.219 --> 07:10.084
Gone through with it.

07:10.847 --> 07:14.135
Yeah. It's the best decision
I don't remember making.

07:16.102 --> 07:18.309
-What about you?
-Ditto.

07:23.734 --> 07:27.226
So, what are we supposed to do now
anyway? Buy a condo and a Cuisinart?

07:27.405 --> 07:30.568
"Supposed to do" has never been
a part of our unique relationship.

07:30.741 --> 07:32.902
We've always made up our way
of doing things.

07:33.119 --> 07:34.234
Yeah.

07:34.412 --> 07:37.119
Including making our big day
the quietest nonevent of all time.

07:37.290 --> 07:38.871
[CHLOE CHUCKLES]

07:39.167 --> 07:41.829
You know, we may be trumped
in the nonevent category...

07:42.003 --> 07:44.164
...by Lois and Clark.
She hasn't called back.

07:44.338 --> 07:48.877
I phoned, texted and e-mailed her,
but it's all quiet on the wedding front.

07:49.260 --> 07:52.593
It's the matron of honor's duty
to get the bride to the altar on time.

07:52.763 --> 07:54.549
So you may wanna reel her in.

07:54.724 --> 07:57.716
My best man duties
are all taken care of. I, uh....

07:58.853 --> 08:00.718
-I picked these up this morning.
-Aw.

08:00.897 --> 08:03.058
-Simple and classic.
-Yeah.

08:04.275 --> 08:07.017
Now get the mice and the pumpkin
over to Cinderella's...

08:07.195 --> 08:09.356
...and get her to the church on time.

08:28.883 --> 08:30.919
GRANNY: I see you're living up
to your Luthor name.

08:31.093 --> 08:34.426
Last heir to the dark dynasty.

08:35.056 --> 08:38.594
I'm rebuilding this mansion
to make it a symbol for something good.

08:38.768 --> 08:42.761
To change the way that people see us
and the Luthor legacy.

08:44.440 --> 08:45.896
Why are you here?

08:46.067 --> 08:50.936
I shouldn't be here,
but I couldn't help myself.

08:51.113 --> 08:52.193
Look at you.

08:55.076 --> 08:57.112
All grown up.

08:57.286 --> 09:01.325
I always wanted to be there for you,
a loving mother.

09:02.250 --> 09:03.615
You were never my mother.

09:03.793 --> 09:06.785
You were special.

09:06.963 --> 09:10.000
Every soul on Earth
charts its own destiny...

09:10.216 --> 09:14.129
...each decision tipping it
toward the light or toward the darkness.

09:14.303 --> 09:16.635
I could always tell
which side of the balance...

09:16.806 --> 09:18.262
...my girls would fall to.

09:18.432 --> 09:21.799
But you were different.

09:21.978 --> 09:27.314
You were born to darkness
yet you yearned for the light.

09:27.483 --> 09:29.815
Being a Luthor
doesn't determine my fate.

09:29.986 --> 09:33.319
Then you must listen to me.
I can't bear to see you suffer.

09:33.489 --> 09:38.779
I want to give your soul eternal life.
Please, Lutessa, let me save you.

09:45.501 --> 09:47.332
[VOICES WHISPERING]
Lutessa.

09:49.672 --> 09:52.505
Darkseid's Apokolips.

09:54.677 --> 09:57.510
Evil in its purest form...

09:57.680 --> 10:00.296
...the heart of human nature
obscured over time...

10:00.474 --> 10:04.387
...as something to be cast away
rather than embraced.

10:04.562 --> 10:09.022
Hades, Kali, even the word Lucifer
is an old Latin phrase...

10:09.191 --> 10:12.399
...meaning morning star,
bringer of light.

10:13.195 --> 10:19.862
I'm afraid the centuries and translations
have twisted Darkseid's true gifts.

10:20.036 --> 10:24.370
But before the end of days...

10:24.540 --> 10:28.829
...his rapture
will be the only salvation.

10:29.879 --> 10:32.086
I will never join you.

10:37.511 --> 10:39.718
Farewell, my child.

10:40.598 --> 10:42.805
Bless your soul.

10:47.563 --> 10:48.894
Wait.

10:51.692 --> 10:53.068
When?

10:53.694 --> 10:57.232
I mean, what do you mean? When?
When is this hell coming?

10:57.573 --> 11:00.280
It's not coming, Lutessa.

11:00.451 --> 11:03.067
It's upon us.

11:57.675 --> 12:00.667
Mom. I thought you were staying
at the bed and breakfast.

12:01.762 --> 12:03.673
I thought I was coming back
to a home...

12:03.848 --> 12:06.305
...that you and Lois
were building together.

12:07.601 --> 12:09.683
We are in Metropolis.

12:09.854 --> 12:13.847
I hope. I sent you a message.
We close escrow in a few days.

12:14.024 --> 12:18.518
Clark, I think you misunderstood
when I sent you the deed.

12:18.696 --> 12:19.856
This is our home.

12:22.324 --> 12:25.691
We've already accepted the offer.
You're in the middle of a campaign.

12:25.870 --> 12:28.031
Just because I'm moving ahead
with my life...

12:28.205 --> 12:31.789
...doesn't mean I'm letting go
of everything that came before.

12:32.001 --> 12:34.583
That was a hard lesson to learn.

12:36.547 --> 12:38.287
Is this about Dad?

12:41.302 --> 12:44.385
I know it's been tough since he died
being the one left behind--

12:44.555 --> 12:46.216
That's just it.

12:46.390 --> 12:48.881
I was never left behind.

12:50.936 --> 12:52.642
No matter where I am...

12:52.813 --> 12:55.054
...or who I'm choosing to bring
into my life...

12:55.232 --> 12:57.314
...your father is always with me.

12:57.526 --> 12:58.777
And he's with you.

12:58.944 --> 13:02.812
If you just allow yourself to see him.

13:04.033 --> 13:05.694
I did.

13:06.035 --> 13:07.821
Last year.

13:08.829 --> 13:11.206
I thought I was talking to him.

13:12.583 --> 13:15.791
But I realized it was just an excuse
for me not to face my future.

13:15.961 --> 13:19.249
Just like I was waiting for Jor-El
to show me the way.

13:19.465 --> 13:21.171
I had to move on.

13:23.552 --> 13:26.760
I'm so proud
of the man you've become.

13:28.933 --> 13:31.219
But why bring up Dad today
of all days?

13:34.230 --> 13:37.142
Because this is a day
to celebrate the next step...

13:37.316 --> 13:40.433
...in the journey you're on.
And everyone who's been a part of it.

13:43.948 --> 13:45.984
And you don't think I'm doing that?

13:46.158 --> 13:49.946
Clark,
you're so focused on what's ahead...

13:50.120 --> 13:54.580
...you're starting to cut out the parts
of your past that made you who you are.

13:57.253 --> 14:01.622
I can't begin to imagine the pain you
see every day when you're out there.

14:01.799 --> 14:05.667
I know you have to put blinders on
to cope with your responsibilities.

14:05.845 --> 14:09.008
But if you turn your back
on all the experiences...

14:09.181 --> 14:13.424
...that made you strong
and compassionate because they hurt...

14:13.602 --> 14:16.810
...l'm afraid that one day
everything you Ieamed in Smallville...

14:16.981 --> 14:18.642
...will have been for nothing.

14:19.024 --> 14:24.189
-l'm never gonna let that happen.
-You already are and you don't see it.

14:24.613 --> 14:26.353
Sweetheart...

14:27.700 --> 14:32.239
...all I'm saying
is you don't have to let go of the past...

14:32.413 --> 14:33.653
...to move on.

14:35.332 --> 14:37.869
Yes, you do, Mom, I'm sorry.

14:38.043 --> 14:42.958
I love you, but you have to ﬁnd a way
to put all this behind you just like I did.

14:43.132 --> 14:45.464
It's the only way to move on.

15:02.276 --> 15:04.892
LOIS: Come on, people,
Air Force One landed an hour ago.

15:05.070 --> 15:08.187
They haven't left the hangar.
This newshound smells a story.

15:08.365 --> 15:11.232
Give me something
I can sink my teeth into.

15:13.162 --> 15:15.904
-No, no and no.
-Look, I know you have a laundry list...

15:16.081 --> 15:19.573
...of reasons not to get married,
but you'll never see the big picture...

15:19.752 --> 15:21.617
...if you get stuck on spin cycle.

15:21.795 --> 15:25.379
There's no Chloe quip
that's gonna make me change my mind.

15:26.967 --> 15:30.130
Clark can hear cries for help.
He's duty-bound to answer the call.

15:30.304 --> 15:33.011
-I won't stand in his way.
-He can't listen all the time.

15:33.182 --> 15:36.515
He's not God. He can't be aware
of every bird or blade of grass, okay?

15:36.685 --> 15:39.643
He's a man.
And sometimes he needs to not listen.

15:39.813 --> 15:44.182
He needs to rest, to love, to laugh.

15:45.986 --> 15:49.103
And when he ﬁnally does decide
to take to the skies...

15:49.281 --> 15:51.988
...he's gonna need you to ground him.

15:52.201 --> 15:54.237
But that's what I'm afraid of.

15:54.620 --> 15:56.611
I'm grounding him...

15:56.830 --> 15:59.572
...keeping him
from soaring to new heights.

16:00.501 --> 16:01.957
No, Lois.

16:02.127 --> 16:04.789
That is so not what he thinks.

16:06.799 --> 16:10.462
But since you're not gonna meet him
at the altar...

16:10.970 --> 16:13.712
...you should hear that
in his own words.

16:24.733 --> 16:26.234
[SIGHS]

16:31.657 --> 16:35.400
CLARK: l, Clark Kent, take you, Lois Lane,
to be my companion.

16:35.786 --> 16:37.572
Forever.

16:38.288 --> 16:41.416
And with you by my side,
I will never be alone.

16:42.418 --> 16:44.579
The world sees a strong
and independent woman.

16:44.753 --> 16:47.415
I've never known someone
with such gentle grace...

16:47.589 --> 16:49.625
...and more pure heart.

16:52.386 --> 16:53.751
When I've been lost...

16:53.929 --> 16:56.466
.y..ou've always been there
to bring me back.

16:57.016 --> 16:59.177
So on this day, at this moment...

16:59.351 --> 17:01.842
...I pledge the rest of my life to you.

17:04.189 --> 17:06.271
You've always believed in me.

17:06.442 --> 17:08.182
And I believe in you.

17:09.445 --> 17:12.528
And when you believe in someone,
it's not for a minute...

17:12.823 --> 17:14.688
...or just for now.

17:15.325 --> 17:17.031
It's forever.

17:26.336 --> 17:28.827
I'm such an idiot.

17:45.814 --> 17:47.679
[DOOR OPENS]

17:53.614 --> 17:56.026
Watchtower,
access satellite Chloe 2.

17:56.200 --> 18:01.285
WATCHTOWER: Satellite Chloe 2.
Access unavailable. Not online.

18:01.455 --> 18:02.695
What the hell is going on?

18:02.873 --> 18:05.831
WATCHTOWER: The satellite
was programmed to disconnect.

18:06.001 --> 18:08.583
We don't have our eye in the sky.
Who gave that command?

18:08.754 --> 18:10.335
WATCHTOWER:
l'rn sony, Ms. Mercer...

18:10.506 --> 18:13.714
you do not have the proper
security clearance.

18:24.686 --> 18:27.018
Link me to Queen lndustries' satellite.

18:27.189 --> 18:31.148
WATCHTOWER: All Queen lndustn'es'
satellites are off-line and inaccessible.

18:31.360 --> 18:34.147
-How is that possible?
-Program command to disconnect...

18:34.363 --> 18:37.776
...came from Watchtower base
at 1242 hours.

18:37.950 --> 18:39.941
Bring up security footage
from that time.

18:40.119 --> 18:41.575
WATCHTOWER:
Accessing.

18:44.915 --> 18:46.576
Oliver.

18:47.501 --> 18:48.991
What did you do?

18:52.881 --> 18:55.088
WATCHTOWER:
Code log display.

18:59.513 --> 19:01.925
Can you access
Watchtower's orbiter's video feed?

19:02.432 --> 19:05.640
WATCHTOWER: Manhunter
has put the new space station online...

19:05.811 --> 19:07.096
...per your request.

19:07.271 --> 19:08.932
Thank God for our favorite Martian.

19:09.398 --> 19:11.138
Watchtower,
show me what's out there.

19:11.316 --> 19:13.307
WATCHTOWER:
Switching video feed.

19:42.181 --> 19:44.422
I've done what you asked.

19:44.600 --> 19:47.262
They won't know
Apokolips is coming.

19:49.354 --> 19:52.687
Our dark lord will be pleased.

19:53.066 --> 19:57.605
Now we ask one ﬁnal mission of you.

19:57.779 --> 20:02.864
To protect the souls we've saved.

20:03.452 --> 20:07.070
This will disarm the bringer of light.

20:07.247 --> 20:09.863
The one who threatens to vanquish
the darkness.

20:24.139 --> 20:26.130
I never wanted to say goodbye.

20:31.772 --> 20:33.808
Then don't.

20:34.775 --> 20:37.357
I thought I had it all ﬁgured out.

20:38.946 --> 20:40.982
How to move on.

20:43.116 --> 20:46.904
And bury my guilt, my insecurities,
my questions....

20:48.580 --> 20:50.696
I'm so close.

20:51.416 --> 20:54.374
I know who |'|l become, I've seen it.

20:56.129 --> 20:58.541
Lois thinks I should let her go.

20:58.715 --> 21:00.876
Mom says I should hold on to you.

21:01.510 --> 21:05.628
You don't need to hold on to somebody,
Clark, if they're already in your heart.

21:06.098 --> 21:08.635
I just can't keep leaning on you.

21:09.059 --> 21:12.472
On Jor-El.
I need to stand alone, you know?

21:14.106 --> 21:15.141
It's better that way.

21:15.941 --> 21:18.307
You mean it's easier that way.

21:22.489 --> 21:24.775
It's just that I've missed you so much.

21:30.747 --> 21:34.581
Then let me be there for you, Clark.

21:35.002 --> 21:38.460
And don't push your mother away.

21:38.630 --> 21:40.871
We're a part of you.

21:45.345 --> 21:47.336
It's like I'm on a cliff,
standing on the edge.

21:47.514 --> 21:50.005
Where I'm looking
is beyond where you've been before.

21:50.183 --> 21:52.390
It's beyond
where Jor-EI has ever been before.

21:55.981 --> 21:59.439
As much as I value
everything you've given me...

22:00.652 --> 22:03.815
...I need to go beyond where
either of you can guide me anymore.

22:03.989 --> 22:08.449
To be the hero
that the world needs me to be.

22:17.711 --> 22:21.169
Why is it that the biggest events
are always the most painful?

22:24.718 --> 22:28.256
You know, Clark, when I graduated
from Excelsior, it was, uh....

22:29.097 --> 22:32.180
It was one of the most important days
of my life, but....

22:32.809 --> 22:36.222
I don't remember
any of the speeches that were given.

22:36.396 --> 22:39.263
I don't remember getting my diploma.
Ijust, uh....

22:41.443 --> 22:43.604
I remember my parents
not being there.

