Today deﬁnitely tops
Chloe's wall of weird.

51:37.469 --> 51:40.802
Exactly how many people
are marked?

51:49.022 --> 51:50.228
More than you wanna know.

51:50.398 --> 51:52.650
[RUMBLING]

51:53.026 --> 51:55.358
Clark, you inspired the darkness
out of Oliver.

51:55.529 --> 51:57.315
I can't do that for everyone, Lois.

51:57.489 --> 52:00.652
If Tess knows how to stop this,
I need to ﬁnd her.

52:01.034 --> 52:03.025
Got a shot
of her car's parking camera...

52:03.203 --> 52:05.660
...and the license plate
of whoever took her.

52:09.209 --> 52:11.951
[RUMBLING AND PEOPLE SHRIEKING]

52:15.632 --> 52:17.497
Our database shows
it's registered to--

52:17.676 --> 52:20.918
-A company called Preclox?
-Yeah.

52:21.138 --> 52:23.550
It was founded only six weeks ago.

52:23.723 --> 52:26.965
According to their bank records,
they have limitless funds.

52:27.310 --> 52:28.641
Genetic research.

52:28.812 --> 52:32.304
I only know of one mega-mogul who's
obsessed with genetic engineering.

52:32.482 --> 52:33.722
Lionel Luthor.

52:33.942 --> 52:36.149
Who knows he's being tracked
by Tess Mercer.

52:36.319 --> 52:38.651
Yeah, but the GPS went down
with the satellites.

52:38.822 --> 52:41.404
This should tell us where he was
15 minutes ago.

52:46.454 --> 52:48.069
Lois, that's the Luthor mansion.

52:48.248 --> 52:50.409
But that place burned to the ground.

52:50.709 --> 52:52.370
Maybe what Lionel's after
is underground.

52:52.544 --> 52:56.332
The Luthor mansion was built
on a labyrinth of corridors underneath it.

52:57.591 --> 52:59.001
[CRASH]

52:59.176 --> 53:00.586
Lois, no matter what happens—

53:00.760 --> 53:04.378
Clark, a person that I greatly admire
once told me...

53:04.556 --> 53:08.390
...that when you believe in someone,
it's not for a few minutes or sometimes...

53:08.727 --> 53:11.469
...or just for now. It is forever.

53:13.732 --> 53:15.973
Now go save the world.

53:27.537 --> 53:29.118
I'll be ﬁne.

53:32.375 --> 53:34.957
PRESIDENT [ON RADIO]:
I call on each and every one of you...

53:35.128 --> 53:37.619
...to stand strong
in the moments to come.

53:40.217 --> 53:44.301
Our military has a precision plan
to take care of the meteor fragments.

53:44.971 --> 53:48.884
We will take swift action
in securing the worid's safety.

53:49.392 --> 53:52.634
A general doesn't miss his daughter's
wedding unless called to duty.

53:52.812 --> 53:53.972
Oh, my God.

53:54.147 --> 53:55.887
Excuse me.

54:03.657 --> 54:06.490
Janet, you're covering
the president's visit, right?

54:07.118 --> 54:09.404
Look, I need you to get a message
to him for me.

54:09.579 --> 54:10.659
JANET:
Hmm.

54:10.830 --> 54:13.492
Look, I grew up in the military.

54:13.667 --> 54:17.159
That speech has buzz words.
"Precision plan," "swift action."

54:17.337 --> 54:18.827
They're gonna nuke that thing.

54:19.005 --> 54:23.123
Only that thing isn't the little meteor
that'll break apart like they think it is.

54:23.301 --> 54:25.758
It's a planet
and it won't even make a dent.

54:25.929 --> 54:29.092
But the radioactive fallout
of this missile, it'll kill millions.

54:29.266 --> 54:31.177
[RUMBLING]

54:31.434 --> 54:32.935
Take it to the Inquisitor.

54:33.103 --> 54:36.186
I've got a plane to catch
with the president.

54:36.356 --> 54:40.474
Okay, well, then you tell him
that he can't press the proverbial button.

54:40.652 --> 54:42.017
Why not?

54:42.195 --> 54:44.356
The Blur will save us
before it comes to that.

54:44.531 --> 54:47.193
The Blur? Oh, my God, Lois.

54:47.367 --> 54:50.700
If you think the president,
his military advisers or anyone...

54:50.870 --> 54:52.701
...is ever gonna take you seriously--?

54:55.417 --> 54:56.452
[SIGHS]

54:56.626 --> 55:00.710
I'm sorry. I wouldn't have had to do that
if the world wasn't in jeopardy...

55:00.880 --> 55:03.132
...and you weren't such a bitch.

55:19.733 --> 55:21.644
LEX:
Hello, Clark.

55:23.111 --> 55:25.397
Can't say I love what you've done
with the place.

55:25.613 --> 55:27.194
Lex.

55:29.242 --> 55:31.324
You still say it the same way:

55:31.494 --> 55:32.870
Astonishment...

55:33.038 --> 55:37.202
...mixed with a hint of dread,
yet with a hopeful ﬁnish.

55:38.084 --> 55:39.540
You're alive.

55:39.711 --> 55:42.168
It seems my father had a--

55:42.881 --> 55:45.122
A change of heart.

55:45.759 --> 55:47.670
And I got a second chance at life.

55:48.928 --> 55:50.884
Where's Tess?

55:51.431 --> 55:52.841
What have you done with her?

55:53.016 --> 55:54.256
She's ﬁne.

55:54.434 --> 55:57.346
I wouldn't worry so much
about my dear little sister.

55:57.520 --> 56:01.388
You know, I used to think it was our
families that made us who we are.

56:02.525 --> 56:05.062
Then I hoped it was our friends.

56:05.528 --> 56:07.109
But if you look at history...

56:07.447 --> 56:11.781
...the great men and women of
the world have always been deﬁned...

56:11.951 --> 56:13.532
...by their enemies.

56:14.162 --> 56:15.618
You have a second chance.

56:15.789 --> 56:17.450
You can change all that.

56:17.624 --> 56:19.706
But that's the thing about memories...

56:19.876 --> 56:22.037
...you can't forget them.

56:22.462 --> 56:25.545
Like how you were always
that one step ahead of me, Clark.

56:25.965 --> 56:28.377
No matter how meticulously
I prepared...

56:28.551 --> 56:33.420
...no matter how strategic I was.
If only I'd known I never stood a chance.

56:33.598 --> 56:35.134
It wasn't a competition.

56:35.308 --> 56:37.299
Of course it wasn't.

56:37.977 --> 56:40.104
You were born to be the chosen one.

56:42.273 --> 56:44.184
You're simply better than us.

56:45.151 --> 56:46.812
And that always killed you.

56:47.278 --> 56:48.814
No.

56:49.656 --> 56:51.567
No, what killed me...

56:51.741 --> 56:54.153
...is that you didn't even want it.

56:54.327 --> 56:56.488
You fought it. You hid from it.

56:56.996 --> 56:58.327
I would have taken it...

56:58.957 --> 57:00.822
...and relished it, embraced it.

57:01.000 --> 57:03.457
My destiny wasn't yours to take.

57:05.004 --> 57:06.710
I get that now.

57:08.007 --> 57:12.000
Which is why
I ﬁnally embraced my own.

57:15.640 --> 57:17.471
You and I...

57:18.351 --> 57:20.808
...we will both be great men...

57:22.939 --> 57:25.225
...because of each other.

57:26.317 --> 57:29.354
We have a destiny together, Clark.

57:31.114 --> 57:33.321
Only on different sides.

57:35.160 --> 57:37.697
And I'll always be there to stop you.

57:37.871 --> 57:39.281
Always.

57:40.623 --> 57:43.365
Oh, I'm counting on it.

57:47.881 --> 57:52.124
Our story hasn't been written yet,
Kal-EI.

57:53.386 --> 57:59.473
And every villain
is only as great as his hero.

58:01.811 --> 58:05.895
But, you see, that all relies on you
saving us from the coming apocalypse.

58:08.735 --> 58:10.396
You know about Darkseid?

58:11.279 --> 58:15.522
You really think I just read
the CliffsNotes of the Veritas journals?

58:15.825 --> 58:19.067
They foretold of a chosen savior...

58:19.412 --> 58:23.371
...the light that will inspire this world
out of darkness.

58:25.793 --> 58:28.205
You're the light, Clark.

58:29.589 --> 58:32.547
Only you hold the power within you.

58:33.301 --> 58:37.510
I'm not so sure that Clark Kent
can save the entire world on his own.

58:38.431 --> 58:40.262
He can't.

58:42.936 --> 58:45.518
But we both know who can.

58:55.114 --> 58:57.730
I'm sorry I couldn't save you, Lex.

59:11.297 --> 59:13.003
OLIVER:
Activate computer monitors.

59:13.174 --> 59:15.335
WATCHTOWER:
Monitors on.

59:17.470 --> 59:19.802
Systems online.

1:00:02.557 --> 1:00:04.513
The day ofjudgment is upon us.

1:00:04.684 --> 1:00:06.220
We've saved the willing souls...

1:00:06.394 --> 1:00:08.931
...from the coming apocalypse
to serve the dark lord.

1:00:09.147 --> 1:00:11.889
Our work is done.

1:00:12.191 --> 1:00:14.182
You can say that again.

1:00:16.279 --> 1:00:18.190
Your mark has been lifted.

1:00:18.906 --> 1:00:20.442
That's impossible.

1:00:20.658 --> 1:00:21.773
Yeah, I got this friend:

1:00:21.951 --> 1:00:24.533
Leather jacket,
blurs faster than a speeding bullet.

1:00:24.704 --> 1:00:26.285
He's pretty good at impossible.

1:00:26.456 --> 1:00:31.621
You were so close
to experiencing the rapture...

1:00:31.794 --> 1:00:34.752
...known only to those
who will be serving our lord...

1:00:34.922 --> 1:00:38.881
...for eternity
while all the others perish.

1:00:39.052 --> 1:00:40.963
[RUMBLING]

1:00:41.929 --> 1:00:43.885
Do you really think you possess...

1:00:44.057 --> 1:00:47.641
...the power to vanquish our lord
from the souls of those he saved?

1:00:47.810 --> 1:00:49.266
No.

1:00:49.437 --> 1:00:51.268
But I got friends in high places.

1:01:39.445 --> 1:01:41.276
You're not authorized to go in there.

1:01:41.614 --> 1:01:44.196
I must have forgotten my hall pass.

1:01:44.367 --> 1:01:45.982
I was just going to the bathroom.

1:01:47.036 --> 1:01:48.276
It's that way.

1:01:48.454 --> 1:01:51.287
Okay. They said that they would brief us
in two minutes.

1:01:51.457 --> 1:01:54.290
It's now been 15 and I really need--

1:01:59.298 --> 1:02:01.675
Do you see that giant molten orb
out there?

1:02:01.843 --> 1:02:03.879
Now, whatever story they told you...

1:02:04.053 --> 1:02:05.463
...it's crashing into the planet.

1:02:05.638 --> 1:02:07.378
[RUMBLING]

1:02:09.559 --> 1:02:11.345
You can see it with your own eyes.

1:02:18.151 --> 1:02:19.641
Hey. Hey, hey, hey, hey!

1:02:21.988 --> 1:02:23.398
-l'm sorry, sir.
-No. Wait.

1:02:23.573 --> 1:02:25.484
I have information you need to know.

1:02:25.658 --> 1:02:27.649
I don't know how you got on
this plane, lady...

1:02:27.827 --> 1:02:30.034
...but you're stepping
so far out of your position.

1:02:30.204 --> 1:02:34.914
All that matters is the truth and you
don't have it. Please, Mr. Secretary.

1:02:38.838 --> 1:02:41.671
I have proof that the meteor
that you're about to nuke...

1:02:41.841 --> 1:02:45.425
...is much larger than you realize
with a density that will result...

1:02:45.595 --> 1:02:48.257
...in you spewing nuclear fallout
over the hemisphere...

1:02:48.431 --> 1:02:50.513
...that could take out
millions of people.

1:02:57.231 --> 1:02:59.096
But you already know that, don't you?

1:03:00.860 --> 1:03:03.067
You all realize
you're gonna be taking out...

1:03:03.237 --> 1:03:06.400
...a third of the Earth's population,
and you're not gonna warn them?

1:03:08.034 --> 1:03:10.025
We can't spread panic.

1:03:10.203 --> 1:03:13.445
It will only aggravate
an already impossible situation.

1:03:13.873 --> 1:03:15.238
And what about your families?

1:03:18.920 --> 1:03:20.751
And the president?

1:03:20.963 --> 1:03:23.625
-Where are we gonna—?
-To a secure bunker.

1:03:23.841 --> 1:03:28.710
The casualties are nothing
compared to losing the entire planet.

1:03:29.138 --> 1:03:30.548
We don't have a choice.

1:03:31.599 --> 1:03:33.885
Now, if you'll excuse us--

1:03:34.060 --> 1:03:35.266
No, wait.

1:03:35.436 --> 1:03:38.849
You do have a choice. Heroes.

1:03:39.148 --> 1:03:42.231
One who will stop this
before you unleash your nukes.

1:03:42.777 --> 1:03:45.564
I know some deeply disturbed brass
have rounded them up...

1:03:45.738 --> 1:03:48.821
...and tried to dirty their names,
but the people had their day.

1:03:48.991 --> 1:03:52.483
And they gave our heroes a chance
to prove themselves.

1:03:52.787 --> 1:03:54.072
You owe the people...

1:03:54.247 --> 1:03:57.410
...a chance to see that their faith
was worth something.

1:03:59.252 --> 1:04:01.117
The world is in crisis.

1:04:01.295 --> 1:04:04.253
This is not a time
for your little hero crusade, Miss--?

1:04:04.423 --> 1:04:07.415
Lane.
This is exactly the time for my hero.

1:04:07.593 --> 1:04:11.256
He will be here.
He will save us. I promise.

1:04:11.931 --> 1:04:13.922
I know you wanna see
your families again.

1:04:14.100 --> 1:04:16.466
You just need to give our heroes
a chance.

1:04:22.441 --> 1:04:24.272
Your heroes have ﬁve minutes.

1:04:56.976 --> 1:04:59.092
[THUNDER CRASHES]

1:04:59.729 --> 1:05:03.313
[DISTORTED]
The last son of Jor-El.

1:05:04.817 --> 1:05:06.148
Darkseid.

1:05:07.153 --> 1:05:10.816
My father sent me here
to protect this planet.

1:05:11.449 --> 1:05:13.656
And I will ﬁght you to my last breath.

1:05:13.993 --> 1:05:16.029
There must be a part of you...

1:05:16.203 --> 1:05:20.993
...that's disgusted by how easily
your people fell to me.

1:05:21.167 --> 1:05:24.079
They may not be perfect,
but I believe in the darkest soul...

1:05:24.253 --> 1:05:25.368
...there's always hope.

1:05:26.255 --> 1:05:28.917
People want to believe
in something greater...

1:05:29.091 --> 1:05:31.673
...and it may be easier to hate...

1:05:32.511 --> 1:05:34.342
...but it's stronger to love.

1:05:36.015 --> 1:05:40.679
Eons have passed
since I came face-to-face with a force...

1:05:40.853 --> 1:05:44.345
...that could possibly tip the balance
to the light.

1:05:44.899 --> 1:05:46.685
You are the light.

1:05:46.859 --> 1:05:50.272
You cast out the darkness
from Oliver Queen...

1:05:50.488 --> 1:05:54.197
...and you will obliterate my darkness
from the rest of the world...

1:05:54.367 --> 1:05:56.858
...if you are not stopped.

1:05:57.536 --> 1:05:59.868
You will surrender to me.

1:06:00.039 --> 1:06:02.200
You will lose your soul.

1:06:02.375 --> 1:06:04.991
I will annihilate you.

1:06:07.046 --> 1:06:11.881
JONATHAN: Clark, you're gonna have to let
Jor-El guide you from here on out.

1:06:15.221 --> 1:06:19.931
JOR-EL: You have always had the power
within you, my son.

1:08:31.649 --> 1:08:33.435
These were my trials.

1:08:33.651 --> 1:08:37.269
JOR-EL:
Your ﬁnal trial is upon you, my son.

1:08:39.198 --> 1:08:41.234
You are ready.

1:08:41.909 --> 1:08:44.696
Seize your destiny.

1:09:30.791 --> 1:09:33.749
Something told me
that I'd ﬁnd you here.

1:09:34.670 --> 1:09:37.582
I combed the lab
and I saw what happened.

1:09:38.757 --> 1:09:41.089
Long time, sis.

1:09:44.054 --> 1:09:45.635
Did you always know?

1:09:45.806 --> 1:09:49.424
Why do you think I recruited you,
treated you as my own ﬂesh and blood?

1:09:49.602 --> 1:09:50.933
You used me.

1:09:51.103 --> 1:09:53.185
Semantics.

1:09:56.317 --> 1:10:00.185
I'd say dear old Dad
did most of the abusing.

1:10:00.362 --> 1:10:01.397
Wouldn't you?

1:10:02.198 --> 1:10:05.190
I guess the bullet in his chest
answers that question, huh?

1:10:08.120 --> 1:10:11.863
He wanted nothing more
than to have you back again.

1:10:13.834 --> 1:10:15.495
And what did you want, Tess?

1:10:18.172 --> 1:10:19.833
Something I'll never have.

1:10:20.216 --> 1:10:21.296
Clark?

1:10:23.302 --> 1:10:24.633
Redemption.

1:10:34.813 --> 1:10:37.020
LEX:
I love you, sis.

1:10:39.777 --> 1:10:41.688
[GASPS]

1:10:47.326 --> 1:10:49.408
You know, I'm actually saving you.

1:10:51.830 --> 1:10:53.536
[TESS GRUNTS]

1:10:57.711 --> 1:10:58.871
From what?

1:10:59.046 --> 1:11:01.082
From turning into me.

1:11:01.632 --> 1:11:03.338
[CHUCKLES]

1:11:08.931 --> 1:11:10.887
It's too late.

1:11:13.894 --> 1:11:15.634
Clark already did that.

1:11:20.734 --> 1:11:24.226
It's the neurotoxin
that you started at Summerholt.

1:11:24.697 --> 1:11:26.437
-lt penetrates--
-Dermal tissue.

1:11:26.615 --> 1:11:29.698
Paralyzing all cognitive recognition.

1:11:32.454 --> 1:11:33.489
How long?

1:11:34.248 --> 1:11:35.613
Thirty seconds.

1:11:37.126 --> 1:11:38.741
What will I remember?

1:11:39.753 --> 1:11:40.959
Nothing.

1:11:42.131 --> 1:11:45.498
The world before this moment
won't exist to you.

1:11:48.095 --> 1:11:50.177
[GASPS THEN GRUNTS]

1:13:34.743 --> 1:13:38.235
JOR-EL: Your journey has come to an end,
Kal-El.

1:13:38.414 --> 1:13:41.827
I shouldn't have tried to push away
my Kryptonian side.

1:13:42.042 --> 1:13:45.500
My strength is accepting it...

1:13:46.004 --> 1:13:47.915
...accepting you.

1:13:48.507 --> 1:13:50.293
JOR-EL:
You honor me.

1:13:50.509 --> 1:13:53.501
A father’s pride cannot be measured
in words...

1:13:53.679 --> 1:13:56.546
...but know that I am proud of you,
son.

1:13:56.723 --> 1:13:59.715
You have no idea how long I've waited
to hear you say that.

1:13:59.893 --> 1:14:02.760
JOR-EL: We have been down
a long road together, Kal-El...

1:14:02.938 --> 1:14:06.101
...one paved with difficult trials.

1:14:06.275 --> 1:14:08.732
Those trials are behind you now.

1:14:08.902 --> 1:14:13.145
Any father can only hope
that he is one day humbled...

1:14:13.323 --> 1:14:15.234
...by the feats of his son.

1:14:15.409 --> 1:14:19.778
But it is your soul, KaI-EI,
of which I am most proud.

1:14:19.955 --> 1:14:22.947
You, and you alone,
possess the courage...

1:14:23.125 --> 1:14:25.707
...the determination
and the compassion...

1:14:25.878 --> 1:14:30.542
...that will be required of you
to lift the darkness from the Earth.

1:15:14.801 --> 1:15:18.293
I ask you to remember one thing.

1:15:18.472 --> 1:15:21.430
Your abilities may be of my blood...

1:15:21.600 --> 1:15:25.138
...but it is your time in Smallville
with Jonathan and Martha Kent...

1:15:25.312 --> 1:15:29.976
...and all the people there
that made you a hero, Kal-El.

1:15:35.239 --> 1:15:38.231
Always hold on to Smallville.

1:17:01.950 --> 1:17:03.531
[GRUNTING AND YELLING]

1:18:11.853 --> 1:18:16.472
This is Lois Lane of the Daily Planet,
reporting from aboard Air Force One.

1:18:16.650 --> 1:18:18.356
PRESIDENT:
Miss Lane.

1:18:20.112 --> 1:18:22.273
Mr. President.

1:18:50.308 --> 1:18:54.142
Come on, Clark. You can do this.

1:19:12.956 --> 1:19:15.663
[CHEERING]

1:19:20.464 --> 1:19:22.329
[LAUGHING]

1:19:33.518 --> 1:19:35.099
MAN:
Yes!

1:20:01.963 --> 1:20:05.547
"And that was the day
the boy turned into Superman."

1:20:05.717 --> 1:20:06.752
Wow.

1:20:06.927 --> 1:20:08.167
[CHLOE CHUCKLES]

1:20:21.775 --> 1:20:23.390
Read it again, please.

1:20:23.568 --> 1:20:25.183
[CHLOE CHUCKLES]

1:20:26.613 --> 1:20:29.901
There will always be more adventures
for another day.

1:20:57.978 --> 1:20:59.593
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

1:21:01.439 --> 1:21:04.306
Did you get it? Thought you
might need something blue.

1:21:04.484 --> 1:21:06.941
I did, just in time.
Thanks, 002. Wish me luck.

1:21:07.112 --> 1:21:08.818
CHLOE [OVER PHONE]:
Good luck.

1:21:10.657 --> 1:21:11.988
Whoa, whoa, whoa, bad idea.

1:21:12.158 --> 1:21:14.945
-Very, very bad idea.
-How many "great Caesar's ghosts"?

1:21:15.120 --> 1:21:17.361
PERRY: Nobody tries to strong-arm
the Daily Planet.

1:21:17.539 --> 1:21:19.825
-lf Luthor thinks he can--
-Four, before coffee.

1:21:20.000 --> 1:21:21.956
Did you get my shots?

1:21:22.127 --> 1:21:25.119
